Alhaji Gambo Salisu has emerged as the Chairman of the New Nigeria People’s Party (NNPP) in Katsina State, to run its affairs for the next four years. Similarly, Dr Sani Umar Kankia was elected as the party Secretary, while the seat of the treasurer went to the Funtua zone of the state. At the party Congress held in the state on Monday, the party also nominated the three vice-chairmen from the zones of the state based on the consensus arrangement agreed upon. Addressing the Congress, Alhaji Gambo Salisu said based on the agreed mode, we are here to solicit and affirm all the Congress procedures to enable us to move forward and prepare for the coming council polls in the state. Also speaking, the interim Chairman of the party, Alhaji Hadi Mai-Dawa, said all arrangements had been concluded to ensure success for the party nationwide. He said with the conclusion of the Congress exercise, the NNPP now has a strong structure across the 34 Local Government Areas of the state and is ready to ensure that, it makes the desired impact across the state. He said the party’s target was to ensure changes and ensure the development of the state and the country in general.